<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>

style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;As from Informatica Data Services/Quality 9.6, a new Rest Webservice Consumer Transformation was introduced, which allows to consume data from Web Services using the Rest protocol.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;This transformation supports both XML and JSON as payloads.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;For Guidance on how to configure the REST Web Service Consume Transformation, refer to the following KB articles:&lt;/p&gt;</p>

<p>&lt;/ul&gt;</p>

<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;This transformation supports both XML and JSON as payloads.&lt;/p&gt;</p>

class=&quot;steps collapse&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel panel-primary&quot; style=&quot;margin:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel-heading&quot;&gt;&lt;h4 class=&quot;panel-title&quot;&gt;I am using Data Services / Data Quality&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel-body&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Web Services Protocol&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;The two main Web Services Protocols are SOAP and REST:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;_Tgc _y9e&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SOAP:&lt;/strong&gt; originally an acronym for Simple  Object Access protocol, is a protocol specification for exchanging  structured information in the implementation of web services in computer  networks. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SOAP&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;_Tgc _y9e&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Representational State Transfer (REST)&lt;/strong&gt; is a software architecture style consisting of guidelines and best practices for creating scalable web services. REST is a coordinated set of constraints applied to the design of components in a distributed hypermedia system that can lead to a more performant and maintainable architecture.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Representational_state_transfer&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;list-group&quot;&gt;&lt;h4 class=&quot;list-group-item expert-question&quot;&gt;Are you using SOAP or REST?&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;list-group-item&quot; class=&quot;steps collapse&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel panel-primary&quot; style=&quot;margin:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel-heading&quot;&gt;&lt;h4 class=&quot;panel-title&quot;&gt;PowerCenter - SOAP - Web Services Provider  - License&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel-body&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;To host a Real-Time Webservice workflow in PowerCenter, it is possible to deploy workflow on the Webservice hub in the Domain.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;The Webservice hub is a service that can be created within the Informatica domain, and does not required a separate installation. However, the required license option needs to be present.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Follow the steps below to verify whether the correct license is in place:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ol&gt;</p>

style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Web Services Protocols&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;The two main Web Services protocols are SOAP and REST:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;_Tgc _y9e&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SOAP&lt;/strong&gt;: Originally an acronym  for Simple  Object Access protocol, is a protocol specification for  exchanging  structured information in the implementation of web services  in computer  networks. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SOAP&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;_Tgc _y9e&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Representational State Transfer (REST)&lt;/strong&gt;: It is a software architecture style consisting of guidelines and best  practices for creating scalable web services. REST is a coordinated set  of constraints applied to the design of components in a distributed  hypermedia system that can lead to a more performant and maintainable  architecture.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Representational_state_transfer&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ul&gt;</p>

style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;When using the SOAP Webservice protocol, the following options are available using Informatica PowerCenter:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Hosting a Web Service: In this case, Informatica will host a Web Service which can be consumed by external clients. There are two types of Web Services that can be hosted by PowerCenter:&lt;br /&gt; </p>
<p>&lt;ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Real-time Webservices: PowerCenter allows the user to create workflows that can be exposed as a Webservice.&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Batch Webservices: PowerCenter has a set of built-in Webservices which allow interaction with the Repository/Integration Service from a Webservice client.&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Consuming a Web Service: In this case, Informatica will connect and consume an external Web Service - acting as a client.&lt;/li&gt;</p>

The Web Services Consumer Transformation that is available in PowerCenter Designer can only be used to connect to SOAP Web Services.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;However as REST is relying on submitting request/responses using HTTP POST, it is possible to connect to REST Webservices using the PowerCenter HTTP Transformation.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;You can refer to the following article in the Informatica How To Library:&lt;/p&gt;</p>

class=&quot;steps collapse&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel panel-primary&quot; style=&quot;margin:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel-heading&quot;&gt;&lt;h4 class=&quot;panel-title&quot;&gt;Data Services/Quality - SOAP - Using a SOAP Web Service Consumer&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel-body&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The SOAP Web Service Consumer Transformation available in the Developer for Informatica Data Services/Quality allows you to connect to an externally hosted Web Service.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;To create a Web Service Consumer Transformation, you would need to obtain the WSDL from the Web Service Provider to import the interface's metadata.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;For detailed steps on how to create and use a Webservice Consumer Transformation in Informatica Data Services/Quality, you can refer to the following &quot;How To&quot; document:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-5417&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Calling a Web Service from a Webservice Consumer Transformation in Informatica Developer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>

<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;3rd party &quot;SOAP/REST Proxy&quot; software is available, which would allow you to translate REST to SOAP protocol, which would allow you host a SOAP Web Service in PowerCenter and have a client using REST to communicate.&lt;/p&gt;</p>

<p>&lt;p&gt;The two main Web Services protocols are SOAP and REST:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;_Tgc _y9e&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SOAP&lt;/strong&gt;: Originally an acronym  for Simple  Object Access protocol, is a protocol specification for  exchanging  structured information in the implementation of web services  in computer  networks. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SOAP&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;_Tgc _y9e&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Representational State Transfer (REST)&lt;/strong&gt;: It is a software architecture style consisting of guidelines and best  practices for creating scalable web services. REST is a coordinated set  of constraints applied to the design of components in a distributed  hypermedia system that can lead to a more performant and maintainable  architecture.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Representational_state_transfer&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Depending on the Web Services protocol you need to implement, different setup/configuration is required.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;list-group&quot;&gt;&lt;h4 class=&quot;list-group-item expert-question&quot;&gt;Are you using SOAP or REST?&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;list-group-item&quot; <p>&lt;li&gt;Batch Webservices: PowerCenter has a set of built-in Webservices which allow interaction with the Repository/Integration Service from a Webservice client.&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ul&gt;</p>

style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;All PowerCenter Webservice Provider functionality is facilitated by  the Web Service Hub Service. To create and deploy Real-time Webservices, ensure that this service has been created and  configured in your domain.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;For detailed information on how to create a Web Service Hub service, refer to the following documentation:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Application Services Guide&quot; href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-13355&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Application Service Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 19 &amp;gt; Web Service Hub&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;To create a Real-time Webservice, a Web Service mapping and workflow will have to be created. Generally speaking, you would create a PowerCenter mapping which contains a Web Service Source and Web Service Target - which would represent the SOAP Request/Response of the resulting Web Service.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Web Service Sources/ Targets can be created from scratch in Designer - or if a WSDL is already available, it is possible to import the existing metadata in PowerCenter.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Once the Web Service Mapping has been created, a corresponding Session/Workflow would have to be created and it is at this stage that the Workflow will be enabled for Web Service use - see the image below:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;For more detailed information on how to create a Real-time Web Service, refer the following documentation:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-12366&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Web Services Provider Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 6-9.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;The following Video Knowledge Base article contains an overview of the steps required to create and deploy a Web Service Workflow:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;iframe src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/ro62Q7f4OIE?feature=player_detailpage&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; height=&quot;360&quot; width=&quot;640&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;list-group-item&quot; href=&quot;#0cf4e360-f7be-11e4-8166-bc764e1028dd&quot; data-toggle=&quot;collapse&quot; onClick=&quot;$('#6da7aca0-be94-11e4-bae0-bc764e1116a6').collapse('hide');$('#eaembedcodecontentcustom')[0].scrollIntoView(true);$('#back0cf4e360-f7be-11e4-8166-bc764e1028dd').attr('href', '#6da7aca0-be94-11e4-bae0-bc764e1116a6');&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right btn-xs&quot; style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;All PowerCenter Webservice Provider functionality is facilitated by  the Web Service Hub Service. To create and deploy Real-time Webservices, ensure that this service has been created and  configured in your domain.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;For detailed information on how to create a Web Service Hub service, refer to the following documentation:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Application Services Guide&quot; href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-13355&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Application Service Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 19 &amp;gt; Web Service Hub&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;To create a Real-time Webservice, a Web Service mapping and workflow will have to be created. Generally speaking, you would create a PowerCenter mapping which contains a Web Service Source and Web Service Target - which would represent the SOAP Request/Response of the resulting Web Service.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Web Service Sources/ Targets can be created from scratch in Designer - or if a WSDL is already available, it is possible to import the existing metadata in PowerCenter.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Once the Web Service Mapping has been created, a corresponding Session/Workflow would have to be created and it is at this stage that the Workflow will be enabled for Web Service use - see the image below:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;For more detailed information on how to create a Real-time Web Service, refer the following documentation:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-12366&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Web Services Provider Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 6-9.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>

<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>

style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;PowerCenter does not provide native support for consuming a REST Web Service. The Web Services Consumer Transformation that is available in PowerCenter Designer can only be used to connect to SOAP Web Services.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;However as REST is relying on submitting request/responses using HTTP POST, it is possible to connect to REST Webservices using the PowerCenter HTTP Transformation.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;You can refer to the following article in the Informatica How To Library:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-8463&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Using PowerCenter as a RESTful Web Service Client&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;list-group-item&quot; href=&quot;#f15c15d0-f7b6-11e4-8166-bc764e1028dd&quot; data-toggle=&quot;collapse&quot; onClick=&quot;$('#f3a7a370-be92-11e4-bae0-bc764e1116a6').collapse('hide');$('#eaembedcodecontentcustom')[0].scrollIntoView(true);$('#backf15c15d0-f7b6-11e4-8166-bc764e1028dd').attr('href', '#f3a7a370-be92-11e4-bae0-bc764e1116a6');&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right btn-xs&quot; style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;PowerCenter does not provide native support for consuming a REST Web Service. The Web Services Consumer Transformation that is available in PowerCenter Designer can only be used to connect to SOAP Web Services.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;However as REST is relying on submitting request/responses using HTTP POST, it is possible to connect to REST Webservices using the PowerCenter HTTP Transformation.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;You can refer to the following article in the Informatica How To Library:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-8463&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Using PowerCenter as a RESTful Web Service Client&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;text-center&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;btn-group&quot; style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;To host a Real-Time Webservice workflow in PowerCenter, it is possible to deploy workflow on the Webservice hub in the Domain.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;The Webservice hub is a service that can be created within the Informatica domain, and does not required a separate installation. However, the required license option needs to be present.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Follow the steps below to verify whether the correct license is in place:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ol&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Sign in to Administrator and open the &lt;em&gt;Repository&lt;/em&gt; properties for the repository you are planning to use. Follow the link to the license that  is associated with this repository.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;https://89175eb808eaf0613315-f3adfb0d864dcb9c0720f4026881eff2.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/license.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;  /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Navigate to the &lt;em&gt;Options &lt;/em&gt;tab of your license and ensure you have the  &quot;Web Services Provider (Real-Time)&quot; option listed as shown below:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;https://89175eb808eaf0613315-f3adfb0d864dcb9c0720f4026881eff2.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/WS.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;  /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;list-group-item&quot; href=&quot;#76ad3ea0-be94-11e4-99b1-bc764e11861e&quot; data-toggle=&quot;collapse&quot; onClick=&quot;$('#48714ea0-be94-11e4-99b1-bc764e11861e').collapse('hide');$('#eaembedcodecontentcustom')[0].scrollIntoView(true);$('#back76ad3ea0-be94-11e4-99b1-bc764e11861e').attr('href', '#48714ea0-be94-11e4-99b1-bc764e11861e');&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right btn-xs&quot; style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;To host a Real-Time Webservice workflow in PowerCenter, it is possible to deploy workflow on the Webservice hub in the Domain.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;The Webservice hub is a service that can be created within the Informatica domain, and does not required a separate installation. However, the required license option needs to be present.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Follow the steps below to verify whether the correct license is in place:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ol&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Sign in to Administrator and open the &lt;em&gt;Repository&lt;/em&gt; properties for the repository you are planning to use. Follow the link to the license that  is associated with this repository.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;https://89175eb808eaf0613315-f3adfb0d864dcb9c0720f4026881eff2.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/license.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;  /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Navigate to the &lt;em&gt;Options &lt;/em&gt;tab of your license and ensure you have the  &quot;Web Services Provider (Real-Time)&quot; option listed as shown below:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;https://89175eb808eaf0613315-f3adfb0d864dcb9c0720f4026881eff2.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/WS.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;  /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;text-center&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;btn-group&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:5px; margin-bottom:10px; &quot;&gt;&lt;a data-toggle=&quot;collapse&quot; id=&quot;back48714ea0-be94-11e4-99b1-bc764e11861e&quot; onClick=&quot;$('#48714ea0-be94-11e4-99b1-bc764e11861e').collapse('hide');$('#eaembedcodecontentcustom')[0].scrollIntoView(true);&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-primary glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left guide-back&quot; style=&quot;color: #ffffff !important;text-decoration: none !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Back&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a data-toggle=&quot;collapse&quot; href=&quot;#039f7f30-be90-11e4-99b1-bc764e11861e&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-primary glyphicon glyphicon-home guide-root&quot; onClick=&quot;$('#48714ea0-be94-11e4-99b1-bc764e11861e').collapse('hide');$('#eaembedcodecontentcustom')[0].scrollIntoView(true);&quot; style=&quot;color: #ffffff !important;text-decoration: none !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Root&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://search.informatica.com/KBSearch#t=Expert&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-primary glyphicon glyphicon-search guide-search&quot; style=&quot;color: #ffffff !important;text-decoration: none !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Search&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&quot;443baed0-f7b9-11e4-82ad-bc764e1116a6&quot; class=&quot;steps collapse&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel panel-primary&quot; style=&quot;margin:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel-heading&quot;&gt;&lt;h4 class=&quot;panel-title&quot;&gt;PowerCenter - SOAP - Host a Batch Web Service&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel-body&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The functionality of hosting a Batch Webservice is included in the basic PowerCenter License. No additional installation is required.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;All PowerCenter Webservice Provider functionality is facilitated by the Web Service Hub Service. To make use of Batch Webservices, you would need to ensure that this service has been created and configured in your domain.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;For detailed information on how to create a Web Service Hub service, please refer to the following documentation:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Application Services Guide&quot; href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-13355&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Application Service Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 19 &amp;gt; Web Service Hub&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ol&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Types of Batch Web Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With the Web Service Hub Server correctly configured in the domain, it will now be possible to consume the Batch Web Service Operations available in the Hub. There are two types of Batch Web Services, defined by separate WSDL's:&lt;br /&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;blockquote&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Metadata Web Services: services to retrieve metadata from the PowerCenter repositories associated with the Web Services Hub. (e.g. list objects in a PowerCenter Folder )&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Integration Web Service operations: services to interact with the Integration service for objects stored in the PowerCenter Repository associated with the Web Services Hub (e.g. start workflow, retrieve session log)&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/blockquote&gt;</p>
<p>For detailed information on all the available Batch Web Service operations, refer to the following documentation: &lt;a href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-12366&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Web Services Provider Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 4 &amp;gt; Batch Web Service Operations&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Testing a Batch Webservice Operation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;942&quot; height=&quot;194&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To test the available Batch Webservices, it is possible to make use of the Try-It application in the Web Services Hub. This webpage will allow you to submit Web Service Requests and verify the behavior. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more enhanced tests, it is recommended using a 3rd party Web Service Test utility such as SoapUI.&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using a Client Application&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;To allow client applications to interact with the Web Services Hub, you can download the WSDL from the Web Service Hub. The actual implementation of the Web Service client would depend on the technology/tools being used in your specific implementation. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The documentation has some details on client application using various client technologies:&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-12366&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Web Services Provider Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 5 &amp;gt; Writing Client Applications&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;list-group&quot;&gt;&lt;h4 class=&quot;list-group-item expert-question&quot;&gt;Did this information help you?&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;list-group-item&quot; <p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Follow the steps below to verify whether the correct license is in place:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ol&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Sign in to Administrator and open the &lt;em&gt;General &lt;/em&gt;Properties for the  Model Repository Service you are planning to use. Follow the link to the  license that is associated with this Model Repository Service.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;376&quot; height=&quot;157&quot; /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>

<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;_Tgc _y9e&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Representational State Transfer (REST)&lt;/strong&gt; is a software architecture style consisting of guidelines and best practices for creating scalable web services. <p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;This transformation supports both XML and JSON as payloads.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;For Guidance on how to configure the REST Web Service Consume Transformation, refer to the following KB articles:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/infakb/howto/6/Pages/17/295525.aspx&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;HOW TO: Configure REST web service consumer transformation to send and receive data in JSON format in IDS 9.6.1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>

<p>&lt;/ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;More information on the REST Web Service Consumer Transformation can be found in the following documentation:&lt;/p&gt;</p>

style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;To consume Rest Web Services using Data Services/Quality, you would need to ensure that the correct license option is in place.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Follow the steps below to verify whether the correct license is in place:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ol&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Sign in to Administrator and open the &lt;em&gt;General Properties&lt;/em&gt; for the Model Repository Service you are planning to use. Follow the link to the license that is associated with this Model Repository Service.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;376&quot; height=&quot;157&quot; /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Navigate to the &lt;em&gt;Options &lt;/em&gt;tab of your license and ensure you have the &quot;Web Service Transformation&quot; option listed as shown below:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;537&quot; height=&quot;222&quot; /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;list-group-item&quot; href=&quot;#983374f0-f7c3-11e4-8b41-bc764e11861e&quot; data-toggle=&quot;collapse&quot; onClick=&quot;$('#032d7f50-be97-11e4-80ad-bc764e1028dd').collapse('hide');$('#eaembedcodecontentcustom')[0].scrollIntoView(true);$('#back983374f0-f7c3-11e4-8b41-bc764e11861e').attr('href', '#032d7f50-be97-11e4-80ad-bc764e1028dd');&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right btn-xs&quot; style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;To consume Rest Web Services using Data Services/Quality, you would need to ensure that the correct license option is in place.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Follow the steps below to verify whether the correct license is in place:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ol&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Sign in to Administrator and open the &lt;em&gt;General Properties&lt;/em&gt; for the Model Repository Service you are planning to use. Follow the link to the license that is associated with this Model Repository Service.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;376&quot; height=&quot;157&quot; /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Navigate to the &lt;em&gt;Options &lt;/em&gt;tab of your license and ensure you have the &quot;Web Service Transformation&quot; option listed as shown below:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;537&quot; height=&quot;222&quot; /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;text-center&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;btn-group&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:5px; margin-bottom:10px; &quot;&gt;&lt;a data-toggle=&quot;collapse&quot; id=&quot;back032d7f50-be97-11e4-80ad-bc764e1028dd&quot; onClick=&quot;$('#032d7f50-be97-11e4-80ad-bc764e1028dd').collapse('hide');$('#eaembedcodecontentcustom')[0].scrollIntoView(true);&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-primary glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left guide-back&quot; style=&quot;color: #ffffff !important;text-decoration: none !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Back&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a data-toggle=&quot;collapse&quot; href=&quot;#039f7f30-be90-11e4-99b1-bc764e11861e&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-primary glyphicon glyphicon-home guide-root&quot; onClick=&quot;$('#032d7f50-be97-11e4-80ad-bc764e1028dd').collapse('hide');$('#eaembedcodecontentcustom')[0].scrollIntoView(true);&quot; style=&quot;color: #ffffff !important;text-decoration: none !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Root&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://search.informatica.com/KBSearch#t=Expert&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-primary glyphicon glyphicon-search guide-search&quot; style=&quot;color: #ffffff !important;text-decoration: none !important;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Search&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&quot;e347faa0-be94-11e4-80ad-bc764e1028dd&quot; class=&quot;steps collapse&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel panel-primary&quot; style=&quot;margin:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel-heading&quot;&gt;&lt;h4 class=&quot;panel-title&quot;&gt;PowerCenter - SOAP - Webservice Provider - Creating SOAP Web Services in PowerCenter&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;panel-body&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;All PowerCenter Webservice Provider functionality is facilitated by  the Web Service Hub Service. To create and deploy Real-time Webservices, ensure that this service has been created and  configured in your domain.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;For detailed information on how to create a Web Service Hub service, refer to the following documentation:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Application Services Guide&quot; href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-13355&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Application Service Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 19 &amp;gt; Web Service Hub&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;To create a Real-time Webservice, a Web Service mapping and workflow will have to be created. Generally speaking, you would create a PowerCenter mapping which contains a Web Service Source and Web Service Target - which would represent the SOAP Request/Response of the resulting Web Service.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Web Service Sources/ Targets can be created from scratch in Designer - or if a WSDL is already available, it is possible to import the existing metadata in PowerCenter.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;Once the Web Service Mapping has been created, a corresponding Session/Workflow would have to be created and it is at this stage that the Workflow will be enabled for Web Service use - see the image below:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;For more detailed information on how to create a Real-time Web Service, refer the following documentation:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-12366&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Web Services Provider Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 6-9.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;The following Video Knowledge Base article contains an overview of the steps required to create and deploy a Web Service Workflow:&lt;/p&gt;</p>

style=&quot;padding-right:5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;The functionality of hosting a Batch Webservice is included in the basic PowerCenter License. No additional installation is required.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;All PowerCenter Webservice Provider functionality is facilitated by the Web Service Hub Service. To make use of Batch Webservices, you would need to ensure that this service has been created and configured in your domain.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;For detailed information on how to create a Web Service Hub service, please refer to the following documentation:&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a title=&quot;Application Services Guide&quot; href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-13355&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Application Service Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 19 &amp;gt; Web Service Hub&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img width=&quot;100%&quot; src=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ol&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Types of Batch Web Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With the Web Service Hub Server correctly configured in the domain, it will now be possible to consume the Batch Web Service Operations available in the Hub. There are two types of Batch Web Services, defined by separate WSDL's:&lt;br /&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;blockquote&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Metadata Web Services: services to retrieve metadata from the PowerCenter repositories associated with the Web Services Hub. (e.g. list objects in a PowerCenter Folder )&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;Integration Web Service operations: services to interact with the Integration service for objects stored in the PowerCenter Repository associated with the Web Services Hub (e.g. start workflow, retrieve session log)&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/ul&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;/blockquote&gt;</p>
<p>For detailed information on all the available Batch Web Service operations, refer to the following documentation: &lt;a href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-12366&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Web Services Provider Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 4 &amp;gt; Batch Web Service Operations&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>

This webpage will allow you to submit Web Service Requests and verify the behavior. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more enhanced tests, it is recommended using a 3rd party Web Service Test utility such as SoapUI.&lt;/li&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using a Client Application&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;To allow client applications to interact with the Web Services Hub, you can download the WSDL from the Web Service Hub. The actual implementation of the Web Service client would depend on the technology/tools being used in your specific implementation. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The documentation has some details on client application using various client technologies:&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://mysupport.informatica.com/docs/DOC-12366&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Web Services Provider Guide&lt;/a&gt; &amp;gt; Chapter 5 &amp;gt; Writing Client Applications&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</p>

No additional installation is required.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>
<p>&lt;p&gt;All PowerCenter Webservice Provider functionality is facilitated by the Web Service Hub Service. To make use of Batch Webservices, you would need to ensure that this service has been created and configured in your domain.&lt;/p&gt;</p>
